eflightnow.com/2026/07/16/live-coverage-spacex-to-deploy-first-starlink-v3-satellites-on-suborbital-starship-super-heavy-flight/", "image_url": "http://spaceflightnow.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/20260715-Booster-20-top.jpg", "news_site": "Spaceflight Now", "summary": "The mission will also test out a series of improvements to the launcher to help push it closer to full reusability. Liftoff from pad 2 at Starbase, Texas, is scheduled during a 90-minute window that opens at 5:45 p.m. CDT (6:45 p.m. EDT / 2245 UTC).", "published_at": "2026-07-16T00:44:24Z", "updated_at": "2026-07-20T14:21:50.589533Z", "featured": false, "launches": [{"launch_id": "ac897b9f-44d2-4ff4-8416-1a0a076e98a2", "provider": "Launch Library 2"}], "events": []}, {"id": 38971, "title": "Launch Preview: Soyuz to launch crew to ISS, Starship to fly another test flight", "authors": [{"name": "John Sharp", "socials": null}], "url": "https://www.nasaspaceflight.com/2026/07/launch-preview-071326/", "image_url": "https://www.nasaspaceflight.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/IMG_0920.jpeg", "news_site": "NASASpaceflight", "summary": "Seven launches are scheduled worldwide this week, including the 13th flight test of SpaceX\u2019s Starship\u2026\r\nThe post Launch Preview: Soyuz to launch crew to ISS, Starship to fly another test flight appeared first on NASASpaceFlight.com.", "published_at": "2026-07-13T20:29:32Z", "updated_at": "2026-07-20T14:34:20.220509Z", "featured": false, "launches": [{"launch_id": "d9adedc4-8fa1-4a36-84f9-43b8893a6865", "provider": "Launch Library 2"}, {"launch_id": "a556b963-0f36-4660-95a8-fdffdba653e2", "provider": "Launch Library 2"}, {"launch_id": "10fa7952-f00b-4292-80a2-4207e208844e", "provider": "Launch Library 2"}, {"launch_id": "ac897b9f-44d2-4ff4-8416-1a0a076e98a2", "provider": "Launch Library 2"}, {"launch_id": "e09f254f-18bc-4985-963e-6075fa3d7a1c", "provider": "Launch Library 2"}, {"launch_id": "beac6ac1-97dd-4eb2-912c-8b4d4d15cd4e", "provider": "Launch Library 2"}, {"l